'''Corvida Raven''' is a writer, technological artist, entrepreneur and public speaker who lives and works out of [[New York City]], New York. She has been garnering national attention since the age of 19 for her blog, shegeeks.net, and other projects aimed at making technological skills and information accessible to the public at large, and particularly to youth, people of colour, women and marginalized communities.<ref name="Hello Beautiful">{{cite journal|title=25 Women To Know: Corvida Raven|journal=Hello Beautiful|url=http://hellobeautiful.com/2011/03/30/25-women-to-know-corvida-raven//|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="the grio">{{cite journal|last=Johnson|first=Keosha|title=TheGrio's 100: Corvida Raven, self-proclaimed 'Oprah of the web'|journal=the grio|date=30 January 2012|url=http://thegrio.com/2012/01/30/2012-corvida-raven/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>
==Background and education== Raised in [[Miami]], Florida, Raven began blogging in eighth grade. She majored in Computer Science at [[Hampton University]] while working at Blockbuster before taking a sabbatical and moving to [[Atlanta]], Georgia. Her trademark plain-language approach to blogging about tech is informed by her experiences teaching family members how to resolve computer problems.<ref name="In Her Shoes Blog">{{cite journal|title=Fly Female Entrepreneur: Corvida Raven|journal=In Her Shoes|date= 24 January 2012 |url=http://www.inhershoesblog.com/fly-female-entrepreneur-corvida-raven/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> Speaking on the challenges of being a black woman in a largely male dominated field, Raven has said: “I do my best to let my passion [for working] with new technology speak for me. I also make a point of highlighting and recommending other women — black, white, Latina and Asian — within my network, because the change starts with me. Sometimes you have to expose others to the things you’re already exposed to. That’s what helps you become successful in an office, boardroom and on the Web.”<ref name="Rolling Out">{{cite journal|title=Corvida Raven Founder, SheGeeks.net|journal=Rolling Out|date= 4 March 2012 |url=http://rollingout.com/2012/03/04/corvida-raven-founder-shegeeks-net/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>
==Career== Raven’s blog, shegeeks.net, is her main platform for educating others about navigating social media, the internet and technological devices. Since founding the site in 2008, Raven has worked as a social media advisor for [[Intel]] and for General Motors' ChevyVolt Unplugged Tour. Once a freelance contributor to Laptop Mag,<ref name="Laptop Mag">{{cite journal|last=Raven|first=Corvida|title=Notebook Reliability Study Ranks Apple Best, Dell and HP Worst|journal=Laptop Mag|url=http://www.laptopmag.com/articles/notebook-reliability-study-ranks-apple-best-dell-and-hp-worst/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> she has also served as Blog Editor for Mr. Tweet<ref name="Hello Beautiful">{{cite journal|title=25 Women To Know: Corvida Raven|journal=Hello Beautiful|url=http://hellobeautiful.com/2011/03/30/25-women-to-know-corvida-raven//|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> and as a Community Manager at ReadWriteWeb, the Industry Standard, Fast Company, and TED. She is co-founder of everythingtwitter.com and the Social Geeks Roundtable podcast.<ref name="the grio">{{cite journal|last=Johnson|first=Keosha|title=TheGrio's 100: Corvida Raven, self-proclaimed 'Oprah of the web'|journal=the grio|date=30 January 2012|url=http://thegrio.com/2012/01/30/2012-corvida-raven/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="Glamour Magazine">{{cite journal|title=Meet Our 21 Amazing Young Women of 2011|journal=Glamour Magazine|date=3 November 2011 |url=http://www.glamour.com/sex-love-life/blogs/smitten/2011/11/meet-our-21-amazing-young-wome/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="mlove">{{cite journal|last=Okolski|first=Ewa|title=Corvida Raven|journal=mlove|date=21 February 2012|url=http://www.mlove.com/corvida-raven/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="Black Enterprise">{{cite journal|last=Martinez|first=Janel|title=Black Blogger Month: She Geeks, The Digital Diva|journal=Black Enterprise|date=15 May 2012|url=http://www.blackenterprise.com/technology/black-blogger-month-she-geeks/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>
==Awards and recognition== shegeeks.net was awarded Best Technology Blog at the 2008 [[Black Weblog Awards]],<ref name="Black Enterprise">{{cite journal|last=Martinez|first=Janel|title=Black Blogger Month: She Geeks, The Digital Diva|journal=Black Enterprise|date=15 May 2012|url=http://www.blackenterprise.com/technology/black-blogger-month-she-geeks/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> and named one of the Top 100 Social Media, Internet Marketing and SEO Blogs in 2013.<ref name="Cision">{{cite journal|title=Top 100 Social Media, Internet Marketing & SEO Blogs for 2013|date=2 May 2013|url=http://www.cision.com/us/2013/05/top-100-social-media-internet-marketing-seo-blogs-for-2013/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> Fast Company named Raven as one of The 50 Most Influential Women in Technology in 2009 and a Social Media Curator to Watch.<ref name="Fast Company Magazine">{{cite journal|title=WOMEN IN TECH: THE EVANGELISTS|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/section/women-in-tech-2009/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="Fast Company">{{cite journal|last=Andrews|first=James|title=FINDING YOUR SOCIAL MEDIA CURATORS: 11 PEOPLE WHO COULD MAKE YOUR TWITTER EXPERIENCE MORE INTERESTING|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/1342863/finding-your-social-media-curators-11-people-who-could-make-your-twitter-experience-more-int/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> She was listed as one of Glamour Magazine's 21 Amazing Young Women of 2011,<ref name="Glamour Magazine">{{cite journal|title=Meet Our 21 Amazing Young Women of 2011|journal=Glamour Magazine|date=3 November 2011 |url=http://www.glamour.com/sex-love-life/blogs/smitten/2011/11/meet-our-21-amazing-young-wome/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> and recognized by Essence Magazine as a Power Player<ref name="Essence Magazine">{{cite journal|title=POWER PLAYERS CORVIDA RAVEN, 23|journal=Essence Magazine|year=2011 |url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/power-players?slide=74288/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> and one of the Top 25 Black Women Entrepreneurs.<ref name="Essence">{{cite journal|title=25 BLACK WOMEN ENTREPRENEURS CORVIDA RAVEN|journal=Essence Magazine|year= 2011 |url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/25-black-women-entrepreneurs/#115676_115656/|accessdate= 16 October 2015}}</ref> Time Magazine's Techland Blog listed hers among 25 Facebook Profiles You Should Subscribe to Right Now,<ref name="Time Magazine's Techland Blog">{{cite journal|last=Townsend|first=Allie|title=25 Facebook Profiles You Should Subscribe to Right Now|journal=Techland|year=October 2011|url=http://techland.time.com/2011/10/21/25-facebook-profiles-you-should-subscribe-to-right-now/slide/personalities/#personalities/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref> and she is a recipient of a 2012 Women Interactive Digital Vanguard Award.<ref name="Black Web 2.0">{{cite journal|title=African-American Women in Tech Honored at Interactive Digital Vanguard Awards & Creative Technology Festival|journal=Black Web 2.0|date= 16 October 2012|url=http://blackweb20.com/2012/10/16/african-american-women-in-tech-honored-at-interactive-digital-vanguard-awards-creative-technology-festival/|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>
