'''Relationship Management Application''' ('''RMA''') is a service provided by [[SWIFT]] to manage the business relationships between financial institutions.<ref name="A">{{cite web | url=http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=57203 | title=RMA – Taking relationship management to a new level | publisher= S.W.I.F.T. SCRL ("SWIFT") | accessdate=2007-05-18 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070218160712/http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=57203 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-02-18}}</ref>

RMA operates by managing which message types are permitted to be exchanged between users of a SWIFT service:<ref name="A"/>
* the receiver specifies which message types are permitted, and sends this permission data to the sender,
* the sender checks the message type against the permission data before sending a message to the receiver.

RMA uses a [[SWIFTNet InterAct Store and Forward]] service to exchange the permission data between financial institutions.<ref name="C">{{cite web | url=http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=61595 | title=RMA Planning Guide | publisher= S.W.I.F.T. SCRL ("SWIFT") | accessdate=2007-05-18 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928013437/http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=61595 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-28}}</ref>

RMA was initially scheduled for roll-out on the SWIFT FIN service as part of the SWIFTNet Phase 2 project in 2008.<ref name="B">{{cite web | url=http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=57205 | title=SWIFTNet Phase 2 – Timeline | publisher= S.W.I.F.T. SCRL ("SWIFT") | accessdate=2007-05-18 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070426040136/http://www.swift.com/index.cfm?item_id=57205 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-04-26}}</ref>

